        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-12-18T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-12-18T16:00:00-05:00" n="181"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d181">
                <head>181. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Delegation at the North Atlantic
                        Council Ministerial Meeting</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                        State</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d181fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 396.1–PA/12–1858. Confidential. Pouched to the other <gloss
                            target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> capitals.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Paris</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1958-12-18T22:00:00+01:00">December 18, 1958, 10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_POLTO1">Polto</gloss> 1759. From <gloss target="#t_USDel1"
                        >USDel</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> Ministerial Council,
                    meeting in restricted session afternoon December 18,<note n="1" xml:id="d181fn1"
                        >The verbatim (<gloss target="#t_C1">C</gloss>–VR(58)68) record of this
                        session, dated December 18, is <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>., Conference
                        Files: Lot 64 D 560, CF 1178. No summary record of this session has been
                        found.</note> after completing action on defense resolution (reported
                        separately),<note n="2" xml:id="d181fn2">See <ref target="#d180">Document
                            180</ref>.</note> turned to draft communiqué. Communiqué was agreed and
                    text is being transmitted separately.<note n="3" xml:id="d181fn3">The draft
                        communiqué has not been found. For text of the final communiqué, December
                        18, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin,</hi> January 5,
                        1959, pp. 3–4.</note>
                </p>
                <p>At conclusion of meeting Secretary expressed appreciation of Council to <persName
                        corresp="#p_SPH1">Spaak</persName> for manner in which latter had guided
                    Council’s fruitful deliberations. Secretary also thanked International Staff for
                    their <pb facs="0440" n="404" xml:id="pg_404"/> work. Secretary said that spirit
                    of unity displayed by <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> at this Ministerial
                    meeting was best guarantee that peace would continue to be maintained.</p>
                <p>Meeting ended at 6 p.m.</p>
            </div>
